&lt;p&gt;The Senior Manager of Product Management owns strategy and execution for their product area. They lead product managers and partner across engineering, design, and go-to-market teams to build products that give customers agency in a transforming industry, using deep customer insight to deliver strategic advantage, not just features. They own outcomes and deliver what matters most with clarity, conviction, and accountability from goal-setting through iteration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll lead product strategy that gives customers agency as legal technology and business models transform around them. You&#39;ll build governance, platform intelligence, and operational capabilities that help customers move from reactive administration to strategic control, understanding how their teams work, where value accumulates, and how to prove platform ROI to stakeholders. You&#39;ll help customers tackle industry change proactively, not reactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be a change agent, leading product teams through AI-driven transformation. You’ll reimagine how we deliver real-time insights and actionable intelligence that helps customers understand platform value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll operate with taste at speed—rapidly prototyping and evaluating multiple solutions, killing most, and shipping the survivors. You&#39;ll move the team from lengthy spec cycles to prototype-first workflows where judgment on working software drives what ships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be a great people leader for your team, developing and coaching your product managers for success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll partner with leaders in engineering and design to prioritize, design, and deliver top priorities within your scope.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll partner across DISCO to launch and create success for your products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 7-10+ years of product management experience with software products, including managing product managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have deep experience building enterprise software (B2B) in complex domains and use a deep understanding of enterprise GTM and customers to drive product and business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve built high performing product teams and organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve successfully implemented product discovery frameworks at scale (continuous discovery, jobs to be done, design thinking, working backwards, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring AI product sense and taste at speed: you understand model capabilities and agentic systems deeply, and you can rapidly evaluate working prototypes to make high-conviction calls on what ships. You&#39;re comfortable moving teams from spec-first to prototype-first workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Even Better If You Have...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built governance, compliance, or administrative products in complex enterprise environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Led products focused on business intelligence, operational analytics, or value realization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shipped products that help customers measure ROI or understand platform adoption patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in legal tech, regulated industries, or domains requiring sophisticated administrative controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Authorization to Work in the U.S.:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates must be legally authorized to work in the United States without sponsorship now or in the future. DISCO is not currently sponsoring visas, including, but not limited to, H-1B, TN, or EAD, and we are not accepting visa transfers.&lt;/p

